    {
      "id": "sybil_16_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_16",
      "description": "Presenting a mechanically sound E46 M3, a pinnacle of atmospheric engineering featuring the S54B32 inline-six with individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. This example features the desirable 6-speed Getrag manual transmission, delivering power to the rear wheels via the M Variable Differential Lock. Recent preventative maintenance includes rod bearing replacement and subframe reinforcement, ensuring the structural integrity of the chassis under high lateral loads. The suspension retains its factory-tuned damping characteristics, providing the precise turn-in and tactile feedback synonymous with the M-division. While the exterior shows minor cosmetic patina indicative of spirited use, the powertrain remains robust, pulling cleanly to its 8,000 RPM redline with the signature metallic rasp of its tuned exhaust manifold.",
